solutions.content:
# Intuition
Basic Idealogy about the lexicographical order of permutations to the given input

# Approach
Step 1:In first for loop, traverse the array from the end to find the first decreasing element from the right.(If any of the element had not been found means, just reverse the loop and exit the program.)

Step 2:In second for loop, traverse the array from the end to find the first element which is greater than the element we had found before.

Step 3:Swap the two elements we had found and stored previously.

Step 4:Just reverse the array from the index next to the first swapped element to the end.


                        Do upvote for me!

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(N)
- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public void nextPermutation(int[] nums) {
        int ind1=-1;
        int ind2=-1;
        for(int i=nums.length-2;i>=0;i--){
            if(nums[i]<nums[i+1]){
                ind1=i;
                break;
            }
        }
        if(ind1==-1){
            reverse(nums,0);
        }
        else{
            for(int i=nums.length-1;i>=0;i--){
                if(nums[i]>nums[ind1]){
                    ind2=i;
                    break;
                }
            }
            swap(nums,ind1,ind2);
            reverse(nums,ind1+1);
        }
    }
    void swap(int[] nums,int i,int j){
        int temp=nums[i];
        nums[i]=nums[j];
