Firstly, we traverse from the end element i.e, 4. 
Find the pnt where the element is less than the next element. here it is-> 2 as 2<3
Code for above two lines:
```
for(pnt=n-2;pnt>=0;pnt--){
if(nums[pnt]<nums[pnt+1]
  break;
}
```
Now if pnt<0 it means the number is in decreasing order and hence, the next permutation will be the reverse of it.
code for it:
```
if(pnt<0)
 reverse(nums.begin(),nums.end());
```
Else check by traversing from the last element the number greater than the number at (pnt) if found then swap them.
Code for it:
