# Only for beginners

**First of all let's we forget about the PALINDROME part of the question**

Let us suppose we have a string of ```Size = 2``` *ab*
What would be its subarrays?
```
2.1]	{'a','b'}
2.2]	{'ab'}
```
Simple right?😁
Now let's try for ```Size = 3``` *abc*
It's subarrays are
```
3.1]	{'a','b','c'}
3.2]	{'a','bc'}
3.3]	{'ab','c'}
3.4]	{'abc'}
```

Take the list ```2.1``` then you can do **2 operations**
1. Add the last element **directly to the list**.  ```{'a','b'}``` + **'c' ->**  ```{'a','b','c'} ```   👈**Boom you got list 3.1**
2. Add the last element **to the last element of the list**. ```{'a','b+c'}```  **->**  ```{'a','bc'} ```  👈**Got list 3.2**

Do the same operation to get others too
**From list 2.2**		```{'ab'}``` + **'c' ->**  ```{'ab','c'} ``` 👈**Got list 3.3**
**From list 2.2**		```{'ab+c'}```  **->**  ```{'abc'} ```       👈**Got list 3.4**


**And this how it goes on**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/5f131924-1510-4709-b6d6-325651f093c3_1641387140.2775264.png)


Now that you have generated **all the possible answers** just check whether it is a **palindrome** or not.
**If any of the subarray is not a palindrome then we can delete that whole vector**
e.g. if ```aba``` is the string then generated answers will be 
```
{'a','b','a'}
{'a','ba'}    //<- 'ba' is not a palindrome so we'll erase this {'a','ba'} whole vector
{'ab','a'}    //<- 'ab' is not a palindrome so we'll erase this {'ab','a'} whole vector
{'aba'}
```
So answer will be
```
{'a','b','a'}
{'aba'}
```

