**Read the below approach to understand the logic.**

***Please upvote if you like it!!!!!***

**Approach:-**
The initial idea will be to make partitions to generate substring and check if the substring generated out of the partition will be a palindrome. Partitioning means we would end up generating every substring and checking for palindrome at every step. Since this is a repetitive task being done again and again, at this point we should think of recursion. The recursion continues until the entire string is exhausted. After partitioning, every palindromic substring is inserted in a data structure When the base case has reached the list of palindromes generated during that recursion call is inserted in a vector of vectors/list of list.

**Dry Run:-**

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/dbedad9b-a814-417f-b23a-ba9cdf252259_1661613943.4511516.jpeg)


**Code**

```
class Solution {
public:
    //fuction to check given range is palindrome or not?
    bool isPalindrome(string s,int st,int ed){
        while(st<ed){
            if(s[st++]!=s[ed--]) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
    //Recursive fuction 
    void solve(int ind,int n,string s,vector<vector<string>>& ans,vector<string>& temp){
        // if ind is equal to n it means string exhausted then push temp string inside ans vector
        if(ind==n){
            ans.push_back(temp);
            return;
        }
        //looping for all char in string which make palindrome sub string
        for(int i=ind;i<n;i++){
            //check if substring will make palindrome, then push that stirng inside the temp and call recursive for further check
            if(isPalindrome(s,ind,i)){
                temp.push_back(s.substr(ind,i-ind+1));
                solve(i+1,n,s,ans,temp);
                // when you back from current call, then pop last inseted string
                temp.pop_back();
            }
        }
    }
    vector<vector<string>> partition(string s) {
        //For storing ans substring
        vector<vector<string>> ans;
        //For temperary inserting and poping substring
        vector<string> temp;
        // Call solve fucntion
        solve(0,s.length(),s,ans,temp);
        return ans;
    }
};
```

