solutions.content:
Hi,
As we need all palindromes so we need to first keep track of indexes that will tell us if substring ```l to r``` is palindrome or not.
So for this we will create matrix say ```dp``` of ``` n*n``` where ``` n = s.size() ```. And in this matrix each entry ```dp[i][j]``` will tell us is ```substring( i to j )``` palindrome or not. 

Note : Matrix is not necessarily needed its here for easy understanding. You can remove matrix and can put palindrome check function ```ispalin(i,j-i+1)``` in place of ```dp[i][j]``` in solve function.

Lets see an example 
- We have ```s = "aab"```.
- Matrix for this will be (here string is not stored in matrix its illustration to understand)
	![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/47bffff1-71b0-4800-9e0e-719316ccda1c_1625195409.9045327.png)

- here 1 denotes that ```substr(i,j)``` is palindrome and 0 denotes not a palindrome.
- now we need to go from ```i=0``` to ```i=n-1``` and push substrings if corresponding entry is 1 else break.
- We will traverse in the following way
- 1. i=0 , j=0
- 2. at this point we have 3 choices either we can take ```substr(0 to 0) ```or ```substr (0 to 1)``` or ```substr (0 to 2)```
	-  1.  we can take  ```substr( 0 to 0)``` because ```dp[0][0] =1```. so if we take it then ```i = 1``` and ```j = 1```
	- 2. now again we have two choices either we take ```substr( 1 to 1)``` or ```substr(1 to 2)```.
		- 1. Lets take ```substr(1 to 1)```.Since ```dp[1][1] =1``` so we can take it and ```i=2``` and ```j=2```.
		- 2. Now we have only one choice ```substr(2 to 2)``` and ```dp[2][2]=1``` so we will take it too. Now ```i and j``` reaches to maximum length so our one answer would be ``` [ "a", "a" , "b" ]```.
		- 1. Now lets choose ```substr(1 to 2)``` after 2nd step instead of ```substr(1 to 1)``` then we can see that ```dp[1][2]=0``` its not 1 that means this is not a palindrome so we cant consider it.
	- 1. Choose ```substr(0 to 1)``` instead of ```substr(0 to 0)``` in 2nd step. Since ```dp[0][1]=1``` we can take it and ```i=2 and j=2```.
		- 1. for ```i=2 and j=2``` we have only one choice ```substr(2 to 2)``` and ```dp[2][2]=1``` so we can take it too. Now ```i and j``` reaches to maximum length again so our another answer would be ``` [ "aa" , "b" ]```.
	- 1. now we are left with one more choice in step 2 that is ```substr(0 to 2)``` but again ```dp[0][2]=0``` that means its not a palindrome ans we cant consider it.
- So we covered all choices and we have answer as ``` [ "a", "a" , "b" ] , [ "aa" , "b" ]```.
### Code with Matrix

```
class Solution {
public:
// define matrix to check palindrome from i to j
    vector<vector<bool>> dp;

	// answer vector
    vector<vector<string>> ans;

	//palindrome function return true if s is palindrome else returns false
    bool ispalin(string s){
        int n=s.size();
        for(int i=0;i<=n/2;i++){
            if(s[i]!=s[n-1-i]) return false;
        }
        return true;
    }

	// temporary answer for each choice
    vector<string> v;

	//recursive function to implement backtracking
    void solve(string s,int i,int j,int n){

	// if i reaches to maximum length that is n then push temporary answer to final answer
        if(i==n){
            ans.push_back(v);
            return;
        }
        for(;j<n;j++){
            if(dp[i][j]){
                v.push_back(s.substr(i,j-i+1));
                solve(s,j+1,j+1,n);
                v.pop_back();
            }
        }

        return;

    }

    vector<vector<string>> partition(string s) {
        int n=s.size();
        dp.resize(n+1,vector<bool>(n+1,0));

        // initializing and filling all entries of matrix
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            for(int j=i;j<n;j++){
                if(i==j) dp[i][j]=1;
                else if(ispalin(s.substr(i,j-i+1))){
                    dp[i][j]=1;
                }
            }
        }
        solve(s,0,0,n);
        return ans;

    }
};
```

