**Approach 2 : Logarithmic Property**
*explain property* -
y = 2^x
take log on both sides
log(y) = log(2^x) -> log(y) = x log(2)
then, x = log(y) / log(2)

class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfTwo(int n) {

        if(n <= 0)
            return false;

		# find x value by dividing log of n and log 2.

        double x = Math.log(n)/ Math.log(2);

		# Once we get the x, we can calculate the exact power of it and see if that matches input.
		# If it does, return true, else return false.
		# converting to int, because it'll give float value. So to round it off, we are type casting it to int.

        return Math.pow(2,(int)x) == n;
    }
}

