**Approach** 🚩 
1:=> Now, we will check the vacancy and traverse the string.
2:=>As string has ',' Commas we need to split it, (we can't use a single char of string as token as there are numbers like 92,934 are a valid token)
3=>We will split the token and put it into a vector.
4=>Now traversing the tokens of vector, for every char we will fill a vacancy so reduce it by 1;
5=>if we have vacancy less than 0, so no space left  return false,
6=>if we have char !=' #' i.e not null, so  it will create 2 vacancy => left , right;
7=>if we have char ==' #' null ,so no vacancy added.

