{
    stringstream ss{p};
	int c{0};
	for( ; c!=-1 and !ss.eof(); getline(ss, p, ','), p[0]=='#' ? --c : ++c);
	return c==-1 and ss.eof();
}
```
**Stack:** time `O(N)`, space `O(N)`

You can keep track current position in the tree with the help of the stack. In this way you can **simulate** insertions into binary tree.

<br>

![image](https://assets.leetcode.com/users/images/3803048b-09cd-4955-a909-bb43cf4269df_1618324945.9085522.png)

<br>

```
bool isValidSerialization(string p) 
{
	stack<int> s;
	for(stringstream ss{p}; getline(ss, p, ','); )
		if(p[0]=='#')
		{
			for( ; !empty(s) and s.top(); s.pop());
			if(empty(s)) return ss.eof();
			s.top()=1;
		}
		else
			s.push(0);
	return empty(s);
}
```

