The idea here is to compute the required nodes for a given node.
For 1 non-null node -> required node count = 2 (including null) .
For 1 null node -> no more node is required as it is closing that branch.
Our aim to check if we have sufficient node count available at every node.

We start iterating, and ignore all the comma character.
Whenever we get a non- null node, we reduce reqirement by 1 and also add +2 because this node will further need 2 more nodes(null/not null) to close
If we get a null node, we simply reduce requirement by one.
Also check if requirement is always non- negative
and after complete check, requirements should be 0

```
bool isValidSerialization(string preorder) {
        int n = preorder.size();
        int req =1;
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(preorder[i]==',') continue;
            else if(preorder[i]=='#'){
                req--;
                if(req<0)  return 0;
            }
            else{
                while(i<n-1 && preorder[i+1]!=',')i++;
                req--;
                if(req<0) return 0;
                req+=2;
            }
        }
        return req==0 ;
    }

