solutions.content:
given traversal is preorder means the order will be
* root
* preorder(left subtree)
* preorder(right subtree)

Similarly we try to find the tree from given traversal by following above pattern.
To do so we can use **stack** here

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Create a node with first value of traversal and add it to stack(here, as of now we haven't filled left and right pointers of this node and we have to keep track of it).

Iterating through array of traversal 
if :  value is not null
then
* create a node and add it to stack.(here, as of now we haven't filled left and right pointers of this node and we have to keep track of it)
* peek node from stack (it will be the root for the first time)
* if  : both left and right pointers are filled 
         then 
         ->we pop that node out and we keep doing this until we find a node which has been not filled with left or right pointer(while loop)
         ->doing so if stack becomes empty then the given traversal is not valid : return false
          ->As we are here then it means that there is a valid node that has not been filled with either of let or right pointer
          ->check if : left is not filled
                   then
                        -->create a new new_node
                        -->fill it to the node.left
                       -->mark that node's left is filled
                        -->and push new_node to stack
                    else
                        -->create a new new_node
                        -->fill it to the node.right
                        -->mark that node's right is filled
                        -->and push new_node to stack

else
*   the process will be same as above for finding a valid node from stack 
    or 
* stack becomes empty doing so then given traversal is invalid : return false
   after finding valid node
    check
        if its left is not filled
        then 
            -->node.left=null
            -->mark that node's left is filled
        else
            -->node.right=null
            -->mark that node's right is filled

```
class TreeNode{
    TreeNode left,right;
    String val;

    //to flag that left,right is added or not
    boolean l,r;
    TreeNode(String val){
        this.val=val;
        this.left=null;
        this.right=null;
        this.l=false;
        this.r=false;
    }
}
class Solution {
    public boolean isValidSerialization(String preorder) {

        String arr[]=preorder.split(",");

        Stack<TreeNode> stk=new Stack<TreeNode>();

        //base cases
        if(arr[0].equals("#")){
            if(arr.length==1){
                return true;
            }else{
                return false;
            }
        }else{
            TreeNode node=new TreeNode(arr[0]);
            stk.push(node);
        }

        for(int i=1;i<arr.length;i++){

            //not possible 
            if(stk.isEmpty())
                return false;

            //considering values and null saperately
            //not null
            if(!arr[i].equals("#")){
                //top of the stack
                TreeNode node=stk.peek();

                //if both left and right pointers are added
                //then looking for another node and remove this node
                while(node.l && node.r){
                    //finding other node if stack becomes empty that means 
                    //given traversal is invalid
                    if(!stk.isEmpty()){
                        node=stk.pop();
                    }else{
                        return false;
                    }
                }
                //if left is pointer is already added then cosider right pointer
                if(node.l){
                    node.right=new TreeNode(arr[i]);
                    node.r=true;//flaggin right of node
                    stk.push(node.right);
                }else{
                    //if node is node added to node then we first add new node left side of current node
                    node.left=new TreeNode(arr[i]);
                    node.l=true;//flagging left
                    stk.push(node.left);
                }
            }else{
                //similar to above but if arr[i] is null then no need to add to stack
                TreeNode node=stk.peek();
                while(node.l && node.r){
                    if(!stk.isEmpty()){
                        node=stk.pop();
                    }else{
                        return false;
                    }
                }
                if(node.l){
                    node.right=null;
                    node.r=true;
                }else{
                    node.left=null;
                    node.l=true;
                }
            }
        }
        //lastly checking if all the nodes in stack has been added with left and right then its good otherwise given traversal is not valid.
        while(!stk.isEmpty()){
            TreeNode node=stk.pop();
            if(node.l && node.r)
                continue;
            else
                return false;
        }
        return true;
    }
}
```

