Every parent node will create 2 spaces for its child node & consume 1 space for itself.
Every leaf node '#' will create 0 spaces but consume 1 space for itself.

Conclusion : Every non leaf node increases the length of the total space by 1 where as leaf node reduces the total space by 1.
So in the end we should left with 0 spaces, whereas at the time of traversal we should atleast have one space to bring other nodes into consideration.

Implementation : 

```
public class Solution {
    public bool IsValidSerialization(string preorder) {
        var nodeArray = preorder.Split(',');
        int nodeSpace = 1;
        for(int i = 0; i<nodeArray.Length; i++){
            if(nodeSpace == 0)
                return false;

            nodeSpace += nodeArray[i] == "#" ? -1 : 1;
        }
        return nodeSpace == 0;
    }  
}
```

