solutions.content:
At first there is one empty position. If we add one '#' null node we have one less empty position, if we add one number we have one more empty position (1 empty position changed to two so there is one more empty position). 

The string is valid if we always have empty position before the end of string, AND there is no empty position at the end.


```
class Solution {
public:
    bool isValidSerialization(string s) {
        int empty = 1, t = 0, n = s.size();
        while (t < n) {
            if (s[t] == ',') t++;
            empty += (s[t] == '#') ? -1 : 1;
            while (t < n && s[t] != ',') t++;  
            if (empty == 0 && t < n) return false;
        }
        return empty==0;
    }
};
```

