Deserialize tree using global index variable. 
The index should be equal to the length of the array got from splitting the initial string. If its not, then you either have too few array elements, or possibly a "#" non-leaf node
```
class Solution {

    int index = 0;
    public boolean isValidSerialization(String preorder) {
        String[]sarr = preorder.split(",");
        preorder(sarr);
        if (index != sarr.length - 1) {
            return false;
        }
        return true;
    }

    private String preorder(String[]sarr) {
        if (index >= sarr.length || sarr[index].equals("#")) {
            return null;
        }

        String node = sarr[index];

        index++;
        preorder(sarr);

        index++;
        preorder(sarr);

        return node;
    }
}

