I used to do this using a stack, but then I realized I could simply do a "DFS walk" over the array which produces a simpler solution, which beats 97%.

```
public boolean isValidSerialization(String preorder) {
	int[] idx = new int[1];
	String[] tokens = preorder.split(",");
	return dfs(tokens, idx) && idx[0] == tokens.length;
}

boolean dfs(String[] preorder, int[] idx){
	int i = idx[0];
	if (i == preorder.length) return false;
	String cur = preorder[i];
	idx[0]++;
	if ("#".equals(cur)) return true;
	return dfs(preorder, idx) && dfs(preorder, idx);
}
```

